{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Let carers keep their allowance \u2013 don\u2019t reduce their other benefits",
        "additional_details": "The clapping has stopped, now please stand up for carers.\r\n \r\nDisability benefits are, rightly, protected from means testing. Not to have done so, would mean that what was given with one hand, would be snatched by another.\r\n \r\nThose caring for many of these people, are not afforded the same recognition. Many will still see their Carer's Allowance swallowed up by reductions in other benefits.\r\n \r\nThis isn\u2019t just about money either, there is a neglectful principle at play; the demoralising dismissal of the carer role and denial of the needs of carers, separate from those they care for.\r\n",
        "background": "Carers undertake daily responsibility for the care and protection of another person. Yet many, forced by circumstance to rely on benefits - so they can be with their cared-for-person - face deductions.\r\n",
